==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Father-in-law
<hw>Fa"ther-in-law`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Fathers-in-law</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The father of one's
husband or wife; -- correlative to <xex>son-in-law</xex> and
<xex>daughter-in-law</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A man who marries a woman having children already, is
sometimes, though erroneously, called their
<xex>father-in-law</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fatherland</ent>⟦br⟧
